    "category_validation": {
      "expected_category": "mpmc_competing_consumers",
      "validated": true,
      "evidence_note": "Repo-wide validation at the pinned commit supports the mpmc_competing_consumers category. Cursory rg scan found many production tokio::sync::mpsc uses. mpsc is central in WAL/ingester writer queues, streaming search responses, compact jobs, file downloads, pipeline batch execution, self-reporting, metadata/distinct value queues, and coordinator/database watch adapters. Pub/sub-style fanout appears in file-list broadcast and coordinator/db watch/event paths, generally implemented with per-subscriber mpsc channels or queue abstractions rather than tokio broadcast. Competing-consumer work queues appear repeatedly via Arc<Mutex<mpsc::Receiver<_>>> shared by worker tasks, including ingester memtable persistence, alert scheduler workers, file downloader workers, self-reporting ingest jobs, and compaction workers. oneshot appears in production for runtime init/shutdown handshakes and query abort/cancellation, but it is a support/control pattern rather than the main architecture."
